cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about improving generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image generation. The paper proposes a new metric called mini-batch energy distance, which combines optimal transport and energy distance in an adversarially learned feature space. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and computer vision, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's focus on stable training with large mini-batches suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics).
